Feb 8 2005	Excellent value. Will return.	I stayed in the hotel for three weeks.1) It is well located. About a three minute walk from Paddington Station, not far from Edgeware road and several supermarkets. There is a laudromat in London Street. One can walk across Kensington Gardens to get to the &quot;Museums&quot;. Surrey Gardens is a quiet street.2) Hotel is clean and changes the sheets and towels every day. Rooms are larger than the hotel rooms that I stayed in Italy. The bathrooms are small. Don't expect a mansion.3) Looked forward to breakfast every day. There is a choice between an English or Continental breakfast.4) Manangent is friendly and helpful.5) The hotel appeared to be the only hotel in the street that was fully occupied.6) The stairs are steep. If one is slightly older, or short of breath then it is advisable to get a lower floor.7) The front door is kept locked and every guest is given a key.	
Dec 16 2004	Breakfast staff outstanding	We stayed there 4 nights from November 25-29th. While the ensuite bathroom is tiny and the shower smaller yet, we always had hot water, even with 4 of us sharing a room. If you do the hokey pokey and wash one side and then another it works. The room felt very warm, and we ended up opening a window to cool it down even in November. Three of our four nights were very quiet. One night we did hear the bell ringing at night and stomping about and doors slamming despite a sign on the door telling people to go to another hotel at night to get a key. So your stay as in any other hotel anywhere depends upon the courtesy of others sharing the premises. Susan in the breakfast room served us each morning with a bright smile and cheery disposition. Full English breakfast consists of toast, tea or coffee, eggs cooked to order, Canadian bacon, beans and tomato. Oatmeal or porridge, orange juice and cornflakes are also available. With that meal to start the day, the ladies often skipped lunch. Paddington Station is a couple of blocks away which was great. While not perfect, the hotel is clean and the staff friendly and I would stay there again.	
